          <colspec colnum="4" colname="c4"/>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>FOCUS and planning of projects</entry>
              <entry>Collecting and processing of DATA</entry>
              <entry>DATA analysis</entry>
              <entry>Communication of findings</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>1.Statement of the problem that will be investigated. The purpose/outcome of the project is to solve the problem.</entry>
              <entry>3.Collecting DATA on the subject, e.g. by using the internet, libraries, interviews, questionnaires, etc.</entry>
              <entry>5.Obtaining results. These have to be recorded, analysed and evaluated. It will determine future planning or a repeat of the process.</entry>
              <entry>7.Reporting. This can be done in various ways, e.g. by means of a written document.</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>2.Formulating a hypothesis*. This makes it possible to predict a possible solution. It can be shown as correct or incorrect.</entry>
              <entry>4.Using data and investigation by means of experimentation, observation, etc.</entry>
              <entry>6.Deduction. This is where the hypothesis is shown to be correct or wrong.</entry>
              <entry/>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
      <para id="id9919282">*Hypothesis: Preliminary statement that still has to be proven.</para>
